{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Even with a college degree, opportunities are still scarce.", "abstract": "Carol Giacomo Editorial Observer examines economic plight in rural Indian village of Bhesda Khurd; notes that young people in village are increasingly despondent about finding work, problem that is endemic to rural areas throughout country; notes that only 10 percent of workers in country of 1.2 billion have steady jobs with legal protections, monumental problem as Prime Min Narendra Modi pursues policy of economic growth.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "18", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Carol", "role": "reported", "lastname": "GIACOMO", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By CAROL GIACOMO", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/16/opinion/in-rural-india-hoping-for-jobs-and-education-in-a-growing-economy.html", "lead_paragraph": "Even with a college degree, opportunities are still scarce.", "headline": {"print_headline": "In Rural India, Hoping for Jobs and Education in a Growing Economy", "main": "In Rural India, Hoping for Jobs and Education in a Growing Economy ", "content_kicker": "Editorial Observer", "kicker": "Editorial Observer"}, "_id": "5506842938f0d85e90e001b2", "word_count": "850", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/03/16/opinion/16EDIT-OBSERVER-INDIA/16EDIT-OBSERVER-INDIA-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/03/16/opinion/16EDIT-OBSERVER-INDIA/16EDIT-OBSERVER-INDIA-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 450, "url": "images/2015/03/16/opinion/16EDIT-OBSERVER-INDIA/16EDIT-OBSERVER-INDIA-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/03/16/opinion/16EDIT-OBSERVER-INDIA/16EDIT-OBSERVER-INDIA-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "450"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/03/16/opi